history.content: I was in the same debate as you (deciding between 189 and 162 when taking 135/wanting to do ML early). I would highly recommend 189 before 162 in your case for multiple reasons. As someone in 162 now, I would highly recommend coming in with a group that you are comfortable with, and you can pick it up semesters after 61C, so have no fear. Sahai teaching 189 sounds invaluable and if you're at all interested in ML, taking it early will open ways to research and there's tons of interesting overlap with 135.

I have been debating whether to take 189 or 162 next semester. I will also be taking Stat 135 and a special topics course. I will have finished Math 110 by Fall 17 and am taking STAT 134, 170, 61c.

Pros of 189

- Learning ML earlier = learn more from advanced ML-related classes (eg, EE 127, Deep RL)

- Prof. Sahai is teaching = Great lecturer

- 189 will complement 135 well

- 110 is fresh in my mind

Pros of 162

- I am taking 61c this semester and material will be fresh in my mind.

Cons of 189

- Prof. Sahai is teaching - might be extremely challenging (not sure)

Cons of 162

- I don't know anyone else taking 162. Might end up with bad partners?

- ML is more important
